# cpltbox API Examples
# Use with VS Code REST Client extension (humao.rest-client)
# Click "Send Request" above any request block

@baseUrl = http://localhost:8787

### Batch request — wait for completion
POST {{baseUrl}}/
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "repo": "https://github.com/owner/repo",
  "task": "Fix the typo in README.md"
}

### Streaming request — live output
POST {{baseUrl}}/stream
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "repo": "https://github.com/owner/repo",
  "task": "Run the tests and fix one failing assertion"
}

### With model selection
POST {{baseUrl}}/
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "repo": "https://github.com/owner/repo",
  "task": "Summarize the project structure",
  "model": "gpt-5.2"
}

### With inline PRD context
POST {{baseUrl}}/
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "repo": "https://github.com/owner/repo",
  "task": "Implement the onboarding flow",
  "prdText": "Users complete setup in under five minutes. First screen collects workspace name and role."
}

### With PRD file from repo
POST {{baseUrl}}/
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "repo": "https://github.com/owner/repo",
  "task": "Implement the dashboard described in the PRD",
  "prdPath": "docs/prd.md"
}

### With skill files from repo
POST {{baseUrl}}/
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "repo": "https://github.com/owner/repo",
  "task": "Build the REST endpoint",
  "skillPaths": [".cpltbox/skills/wp-rest-api/SKILL.md"]
}

### Complex workflow with streaming
POST {{baseUrl}}/stream
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "repo": "https://github.com/owner/repo",
  "task": "Resolve issue #123. Open or update a PR, respond to feedback, and continue until done.",
  "prdPath": "docs/prd-github-issue-pr-loop.md"
}
